The paper deals with the $k$-nearest neighbor model, which is a fundamental concept in many areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), document retrieval (cs.IR), and similarity search (cs.SI). The paper presents a property testing algorithm for $k$-NN graphs, which is a graph-based representation of the $k$-NN model, and evaluates it empirically on $k$-NN models computed by various algorithms. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to multiple sub-categories of arXiv CS.
